OL,3,CTV-related anniversaries for 22 MAR
OL,4,CPROGRAMMES
OL,5,
OL,6,CG1957FThe Tonight programme includes a
OL,7,Fshort news summary for the first time.
OL,8,
OL,9,FThe change was instigated by editor
OL,10,FDonald Baverstock. It was transmitted
OL,11,Ffrom Egton House (later home to BBC
OL,12,FRadio 1) and was presented by a senior
OL,13,Fduty news editor. Gavin Gray presented
OL,14,Fthe first news summary.
OL,15,
OL,16,FOther presenters of the summary
OL,17,Fincluded Palmer (Ritz) Ritzema and John
OL,18,FMackinnon, in what turned out to be a
OL,19,Fshort-lived experiment.
OL,20,
OL,21,FGavin Gray presented the final news
OL,22,Fsummary on 21st August 1957.
OL,23,Sppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
